ixed relay on Saturday.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.864090672489252e-16, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men's 100m final - 8:50pm  The blue riband event of athletics programme has lost a little of its shine in the post-Usain Bolt years, but this weekend's final could throw up a box office clash between America's Noah Lyles and the most exciting Jamaican sprint talent to emerge since the great man retired.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9975086239166167, \"rank\": 0.0024975976872649835, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kishane Thompson ran a blistering 9.77seconds at his county's national trials in Kingston and comes in as the fastest man in the world this year, albeit one of ten to have gone quicker than 9.9.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.